th special guests such as Bileko, Kersi, and many others. In 2012, he took the plunge and moved to Los Angeles, where he surprised with his quirky, multicultural Afro-European universe, drawn from so many minorities. In 2016, Julien became a semi-finalist at the LA Funniest Comics, and participated in the “Funniest Person in the World Contest” at the legendary Laugh Factory. While continuing on his hard work, in 2019 Julien was again invited to perform at the famous Laugh Factory for “Chocolate Sundaes”. Julien is represented by Chris Saavedra from Saint Agency in Los Angeles. His obvious talent will definitely pave ways for him and we can’t wait to see where he places in the nearest future. VANGUARD “We dey fine, no wahala,” Julien Tetrault replied as he answered a telephone call. Everybody around was surprised. The Canadian has not been long in Nigeria but he is quickly adapting to ways of life here. May 21, 2016 In "News" Bright Okpocha aka Basketmouth is one of the biggest exporter of comedy in Nigeria today, making millions of naira wherever he goes through his shows and business deals. Basketmouth didn’t plan to become a comedian, but a rap artiste. July 26, 2014 In "Showtime People" Comedy business is bound to take a new dimension as a pioneer filmmaker and comedy merchant extra-ordinaire, Opa Williams has unveiled plans to export his brainchild comedy show, “ Nite of a Thousand Laughs”to other African countries . The countries include Kenya, Uganda, Tanzania, Liberia amongst others. May 22, 2011 In "Entertainment"